#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:4
msgid "fish_opt - create an option specification for the argparse command"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:7
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:9
msgid ""
"fish_opt [(-slor | --multiple-vals=) OPTNAME]\n"
"fish_opt --help"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:15
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:17
msgid ""
"This command provides a way to produce option specifications suitable for "
"use with the :doc:`argparse <argparse>` command. You can, of course, write "
"the option specifications by hand without using this command. But you might "
"prefer to use this for the clarity it provides."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:19
msgid "The following ``argparse`` options are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:21
msgid "**-s** or **--short**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:22
msgid ""
"Takes a single letter that is used as the short flag in the option being "
"defined. This option is mandatory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:24
msgid "**-l** or **--long**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:25
msgid ""
"Takes a string that is used as the long flag in the option being defined. "
"This option is optional and has no default. If no long flag is defined then "
"only the short flag will be allowed when parsing arguments using the option "
"specification."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:27
msgid "**--long-only**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:28
msgid ""
"The option being defined will only allow the long flag name to be used. The "
"short flag name must still be defined (i.e., **--short** must be specified) "
"but it cannot be used when parsing arguments using this option specification."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:30
msgid "**-o** or **--optional-val**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:31
msgid ""
"Tthe option being defined can take a value, but it is optional rather than "
"required. If the option is seen more than once when parsing arguments, only "
"the last value seen is saved. This means the resulting flag variable created "
"by ``argparse`` will zero elements if no value was given with the option "
"else it will have exactly one element."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:33
msgid "**-r** or **--required-val**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:34
msgid ""
"The option being defined requires a value. If the option is seen more than "
"once when parsing arguments, only the last value seen is saved. This means "
"the resulting flag variable created by ``argparse`` will have exactly one "
"element."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:36
msgid "**--multiple-vals**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:37
msgid ""
"The option being defined requires a value each time it is seen. Each "
"instance is stored. This means the resulting flag variable created by "
"``argparse`` will have one element for each instance of this option in the "
"arguments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:39
msgid "**-h** or **--help**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:40
msgid "Displays help about using this command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:43
msgid "Examples"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:45
msgid "Define a single option specification for the boolean help flag:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:51
msgid ""
"set -l options (fish_opt -s h -l help)\n"
"argparse $options -- $argv"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:55
msgid "Same as above but with a second flag that requires a value:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:61
msgid ""
"set -l options (fish_opt -s h -l help)\n"
"set options $options (fish_opt -s m -l max --required-val)\n"
"argparse $options -- $argv"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:66
msgid ""
"Same as above but with a third flag that can be given multiple times saving "
"the value of each instance seen and only the long flag name (``--token``) "
"can be used:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_opt.rst:72
msgid ""
"set -l options (fish_opt --short=h --long=help)\n"
"set options $options (fish_opt --short=m --long=max --required-val)\n"
"set options $options (fish_opt --short=t --long=token --multiple-vals --long-"
"only)\n"
"argparse $options -- $argv"
msgstr ""
